== 評價 ==

===正面===

技术作家{{tsl|en|Glyn Moody|格林·穆迪}}于2011年5月描述了树莓派是一个“潜在的[[BBC_Micro|BBC Micro]]2.0”项目，不是要取代而是要补充PC兼容机。<ref name="computerworlduk as british">{{cite web | url=http://blogs.computerworlduk.com/open-enterprise/2011/05/as-british-as-raspberry-pi | title=As British as Raspberry Pi? | publisher=[[Computerworld|Computerworld]] | work=Computerworld UK Open Enterprise blog | date=2011-05-09 | accessdate=2012-02-02 | author=Moody Glyn | authorlink=Glyn Moody | archive-date=2013-01-02 | archive-url=https://archive.is/20130102155751/http://blogs.computerworlduk.com/open-enterprise/2011/05/as-british-as-raspberry-pi | dead-url=yes }}</ref>在2012年3月在''ITPRO''上，斯蒂芬·普里查德（Stephen Pritchard）呼应了“BBC Micro的接班人”的情绪。<ref name="itpro bbc 2012">{{cite news | url=http://www.itpro.co.uk/639292/raspberry-pi-a-bbc-micro-for-todays-generation | title=Raspberry Pi: A BBC Micro for today's generation | work=[[ITPRO|ITPRO]] | date=2012-03-01 | accessdate=2012-03-15 | author=Pritchard, Stephen | archive-date=2020-10-01 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201001201819/https://www.itpro.co.uk/639292/raspberry-pi-a-bbc-micro-for-todays-generation | dead-url=no }}</ref> 

在英国的[[電腦歷史博物館|電腦歷史博物館]]大力支持树莓派项目，感觉是它可以“迎来一个新的时代”<ref name="computinghistory donated">{{cite web | url=http://www.computinghistory.org.uk/news/16944/ | title=One of the First Raspberry Pi Computers Donated to Museum | publisher=[[The_Centre_for_Computing_History|The Centre for Computing History]] | date=2012-01-09 | accessdate=2012-02-28 | archive-date=2014-03-27 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140327011629/http://www.computinghistory.org.uk/news/16944/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。在发布之前，树莓派板子被展示给在剑桥的[[ARM|ARM]]首席执行官Warren East，概述了谷歌的想法，以提高英国科学和技术教育。<ref name="cabume improve stem teaching">{{cite news | url=http://www.cabume.co.uk/the-cluster/how-google-can-really-help-improve-stem-teaching-in-the-uk.html | title=How Google can really help improve STEM teaching in the UK | work=Cabume | date=2012-02-23 | accessdate=2012-02-28 | author=Osborn, George | archive-date=2012-03-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302104327/http://www.cabume.co.uk/the-cluster/how-google-can-really-help-improve-stem-teaching-in-the-uk.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>{{tsl|en|Next Gen report|次世代报告}}的合著者，Alex Hope，认为儿童接触计算机编程的兴奋是充满希望。<ref name="telegraph ">{{cite news | url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/video-games/8931387/Computing-classes-dont-teach-programming-skills.html | title=Computing classes don't teach programming skills | work=The Daily Telegraph | date=2011-12-03 | accessdate=2012-02-27 | author=Stanford, Peter | location=London | archive-date=2021-03-09 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309061955/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/video-games/8931387/Computing-classes-dont-teach-programming-skills.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>

在2012年10月树莓派赢得了T3的“年度创新奖”。<ref>{{cite web|title=Raspberry Pi - Innovation of the Year|url=http://awards.t3.com/categories/innovation-of-the-year/raspberry-pi|publisher=T3 Gadget Awards|accessdate=2012-10-09|archive-date=2012-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120628193010/http://awards.t3.com/categories/innovation-of-the-year/raspberry-pi|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===负面===

然而，Harry Fairhead表明更多的重点应放在提高现有硬件上提供的教育软件， 例如，利用类似于谷歌手机编程软件工具（[[Google_App_Inventor|Google App Inventor]]）让编写程序返回学校，而不是增加新的硬件选择<ref name="Raspberry Pi or Programming">{{cite news | url=http://www.i-programmer.info/professional-programmer/i-programmer/3419-raspberry-pi-or-programming.html | title=Raspberry Pi or Programming – What shall we teach the children? | work=I Programmer | date=2011-12-02 | accessdate=2012-02-07 | author=Fairhead, Harry | archive-date=2019-04-03 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403051155/https://www.i-programmer.info/professional-programmer/i-programmer/3419-raspberry-pi-or-programming.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[ZDnet|ZDnet]]网站的文章作者之一Simon Rockman认为，青少年将"有更好的事情要做"，不用管在20世纪80年代发生的事。<ref name="zdnet mid-life crisis">{{cite web | url=http://www.zdnet.co.uk/blogs/fuss-free-phones-simon-rockman-10024919/is-raspberry-pi-a-mid-life-crisis-10025449/ | title=Is raspberry pi a mid-life crisis? | publisher=[[ZDNet|ZDNet]] | date=2012-02-21 | accessdate=2012-02-24 | author=Rockman, Simon | quote=Just because young teens led the way in computing in the 1980s doesn’t mean it should, will or can happen again. Those outside the tech age bubble have better things to do. | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120223123751/http://www.zdnet.co.uk/blogs/fuss-free-phones-simon-rockman-10024919/is-raspberry-pi-a-mid-life-crisis-10025449/ | archivedate=2012-02-23 }}</ref>

一些开源项目批评了缺乏可用的硬件文档（树莓派网站上的常见问题，[[博通|博通]]（Broadcom）公司没有为了BCM2835发布一个完整的data sheet），这可用的硬件文档发布本应该将使得其他操作系统移植到树莓派变得更容易。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mail-index.netbsd.org/port-arm/2012/07/04/msg001363.html|title=Raspberry Pi Hardware Donation|access-date=2012-10-23|archive-date=2021-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210305005426/http://mail-index.netbsd.org/port-arm/2012/07/04/msg001363.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://marc.info/?l=openbsd-misc&m=132788027403910&w=2|title=looking for hardware recommendations, x86 or otherwise.|access-date=2012-10-23|archive-date=2021-02-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210226131500/https://marc.info/?l=openbsd-misc&m=132788027403910&w=2|dead-url=no}}</ref>

